StringLiteralExpr.value: Input data must have at least 3 valid values.
The second input "alpha" must be within 0 and 0.5 .
To work with different values of alpha the statistic_toolbox is needed.
Without that toolbox the only available value for alpha is 0.01 (1%).
Allowed values for ''pri'' are only 0 (do not plot) and 1 (plot)
the method parameter has a wrong value; permitted values are: ''mean'', ''median'', ''biweight''
